As an administrator, I think it would be beneficial to allow for bulk updates in Portfolio live plans, such as allowing a user to update members/teams for all epics and stories under a specific release. I'm not aware of a mechanism currently in place for this, but it might be worth looking into.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1867].
  {panel}

Currently, if Portfolio is attempting to schedule a story and a sprint already has work items booked and cannot fit the entire story, the story will attempt to be scheduled in the next available sprint that can fit the full estimate of the story. Portfolio will then split it into multiple sprints if it cannot fit into a full empty sprint.

As an admin, I believe it would be useful to allow Portfolio to book stories immediately, even if the next available sprint does not have the complete amount of capacity necessary to complete the story, and then split them into other sprints accordingly. Having an option to do this would also be useful.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1866].
  {panel}

It would be helpful within the Gantt chart to allow the user to optionally present the actual start/end dates and logged work over the top of the duration of an issue.  Attached is a sample of how it might look.  This way the entire status can be included in a single Gantt view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
