Currently while going through the motions of creating a plan, the UI shows releases that are out the door and still in the project.  This becomes a pain to look for the new ones you want to create the plan for.  The only way to not show is to archive that release in the project but that will prevent from adding that version to affects version(s) field for any new issues coming from a customer or reported internally.

It would be great if there is a switch to show only unreleased versions in LP or it automatically removes them from the UI during plan creation.

